#Introduction
-----------------------
This is testbench template for Efinix SOC. Modelsim run script is provided. Modify run.sh or run.bat to change other simulator run script.

#Installation
-----------------------
1.  Open run.bat or run.sh
2.  Check for PATH variable, add directory path of your simulator to this PATH variable.

#How to use
-----------------------
1.  Copy software user app binary file to "tb" folder. By default, blinkAndEcho.bin app is provided.
2a. For Windows user, double click run.bat to start run the simulation.
2b. For Linux user, execute './run.sh' to start run the simulation.

#How to target user app
-----------------------
1.  Open run.bat or run.sh
2.  Check for MyApp variable, modify it to your app's name.

#Note
-----------------------
1.  Ruby SOC simulation bypass SPI flash offloading process, thus do not use *.bin in "tb" folder in real hardware     implementation.
2.  Ruby SOC simulation is using simple RAM model instead of DDR model.
3.  If you are required to run simulation with item (1) and (2), please contact Efinix for support.
